MS NID 16/17

NID 16 'Saira ExtraCondensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Saira ExtraCondensed Thin'.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Saira ExtraCondensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Saira ExtraCondensed ExtraLight'.

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'SairaExtraCondensed-Light', Everything looks good.

Saira ExtraCondensed Light Regular (SairaExtraCondensed-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'SairaExtraCondensed-Light', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Saira ExtraCondensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Saira ExtraCondensed Light'.

OK: Font has both Typographic Family Name (NID 16) and Typographic Subfamily Name (NID 17).

Saira ExtraCondensed Medium Regular (SairaExtraCondensed-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Saira ExtraCondensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Saira ExtraCondensed Medium'.

Pass

NID 6 is 'SairaExtraCondensed-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Saira ExtraCondensed SemiBold Regular (SairaExtraCondensed-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'SairaExtraCondensed-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Saira ExtraCondensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Saira ExtraCondensed SemiBold'.

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'SairaExtraCondensed-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Saira ExtraCondensed ExtraBold Regular (SairaExtraCondensed-ExtraBold.ttf)

'space' in NID 6 cause issues in fontbook for Mac.

NID 6 is 'SairaExtraCondensed-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'SairaExtraCondensed-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Saira ExtraCondensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Saira ExtraCondensed ExtraBold'.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Saira ExtraCondensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Saira ExtraCondensed Black'.
